{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "02", "m": "04", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "04", "M": "17", "S": "41"}}, "news": [{"title": "Andheri East tops in property tax collection in FY26, Lower Parel next in Mumbai", "para": "Mumbai's K-East ward led property tax collections for 2025-26, contributing to the BMC's record Rs 7,610.9 crore revenue. This achievement, surpassing targets, was driven by aggressive recovery drives and improved payment systems. Western suburbs dominated collections, highlighting property tax's crucial role as the BMC's primary income source.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/andheri-east-leads-mumbai-in-property-tax-collection-for-2025-26/129967118?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-132056/129967118.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Pune civic body misses revenue target for FY26 by \u20b93,400 crore", "para": "Pune Municipal Corporation fell short of its Rs 12,600 crore revenue target for FY 2025-26, collecting only Rs 9,200 crore. A significant deficit stemmed from building permissions and property tax recovery issues, particularly in newly merged areas. Activists criticized reliance on amnesty schemes over strict action against defaulters.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/pune-municipal-corporation-faces-3400-crore-revenue-shortfall-in-fy26/129967071?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-96144/129967071.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Noida records highest stamp duty collections in a decade, but property registration slows", "para": "Noida's stamp and registration department achieved its highest revenue in a decade, collecting Rs 4,498.7 crore in FY 2025-26, despite a dip in property registrations. This success was driven by state government rebates on stamp duty for women and reduced fees for rental and family property transfers.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/noida-sees-decade-high-stamp-duty-collections-amid-property-registration-decline/129966971?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-54964/129966971.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}